.TH limits 4
.SH NAME
\*Llimits\*O \- Header files for implementation-specific constants
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.iX "limits.h header file"
.iX "header files" "limits.h"
.sS
\*L#include <limits.h>\*O
.nL
\*L#include <float.h>\*O
.nL
\*L#include <sys/limits.h>\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The header file \*Llimits.h\*O specifies the sizes of integral types as
required by the proposed ANSI C standard.
The header file \*Lfloat.h\*O
specifies the characteristics of floating types as required by
the proposed ANSI C standard.
The constants that refer to long doubles that should appear in
\*Lfloat.h\*O are not specified because long doubles are not implemented.
The header file \*Lsys/limits.h\*O
is a list of magnitude limitations imposed by a specific implementation of
the operating system.  All values in the files are specified in decimal.
